/*This is an edited CSS userscript for Mozilla Firefox.
Original version is "TinyCSS" of DeviantArt user noha-ra,
found here: http://noha-ra.deviantart.com/art/Tinycss-476413072

To use this, install the "Stylish" add-on. You will also need
the "WeblySleek UI" typeface. If you are on Arch Linux, install
"ttf-weblysleekui"" from AUR.

IF YOU ARE ON WINDOWS: Yes you can use this. Just replace all
occurrances of "weblysleek ui normal" with "segoe ui", it's a
similar typeface. Also set the font size to 11. You may or may
not have to set the URL bar height (line 188) to 17 if it's larger
than the background bar - this was the case for me.*/


